{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":17000,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":409000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":432000,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":434000,"text":"Imagining a solo cello concert,"},{"time":437000,"text":"one would most likely think of Johann Sebastian Bach"},{"time":440000,"text":"unaccompanied cello suites."},{"time":443000,"text":"As a child"},{"time":445000,"text":"studying these eternal masterpieces,"},{"time":448000,"text":"Bach's music would intermingle"},{"time":450000,"text":"with the singing voices of Muslim prayers"},{"time":453000,"text":"from the neighboring Arab village"},{"time":455000,"text":"of the northern Kibbutz in Israel"},{"time":457000,"text":"where I grew up."},{"time":459000,"text":"Late at night, after hours of practicing,"},{"time":461000,"text":"I would listen to Janis Joplin and Billie Holiday"},{"time":464000,"text":"as the sounds of tango music"},{"time":466000,"text":"would be creeping from my parents' stereo."},{"time":469000,"text":"It all became music to me."},{"time":472000,"text":"I didn't hear the boundaries."}]},{"cues":[{"time":475000,"text":"I still start every day"},{"time":477000,"text":"practicing playing Bach."},{"time":479000,"text":"His music never ceases"},{"time":481000,"text":"to sound fresh and surprising to me."},{"time":483000,"text":"But as I was moving away"},{"time":485000,"text":"from the traditional classical repertoire"},{"time":487000,"text":"and trying to find new ways"},{"time":489000,"text":"of musical expression,"},{"time":491000,"text":"I realized that with today's technological resources,"},{"time":494000,"text":"there's no reason to limit"},{"time":496000,"text":"what can be produced at one time"},{"time":499000,"text":"from a single string instrument."}]},{"cues":[{"time":501000,"text":"The power and coherency"},{"time":503000,"text":"that comes from one person hearing, perceiving and playing all the voices"},{"time":507000,"text":"makes a very different experience."},{"time":510000,"text":"The excitement of a great orchestra performance"},{"time":513000,"text":"comes from the attempt to have a collective of musicians"},{"time":516000,"text":"producing one unified whole concept."},{"time":519000,"text":"The excitement from using multi-tracking,"},{"time":522000,"text":"the way I did in the piece you will hear next,"},{"time":526000,"text":"comes from the attempt"},{"time":528000,"text":"to build and create a whole universe"},{"time":531000,"text":"with many diverse layers,"},{"time":534000,"text":"all generated from a single source."},{"time":537000,"text":"My cello and my voice are layered"},{"time":539000,"text":"to create this large sonic canvas."}]},{"cues":[{"time":542000,"text":"When composers write music for me,"},{"time":545000,"text":"I ask them to forget what they know about the cello."},{"time":547000,"text":"I hope to arrive at new territories"},{"time":550000,"text":"to discover sounds I have never heard before."},{"time":553000,"text":"I want to create endless possibilities"},{"time":555000,"text":"with this cello."},{"time":557000,"text":"I become the medium through which the music is being channeled,"},{"time":560000,"text":"and in the process, when all is right,"},{"time":563000,"text":"the music is transformed"},{"time":565000,"text":"and so am I."}]},{"cues":[{"time":574000,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1184000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}